* CliAIRPERSON.-The Chairman of the Council, in consultation with the Committee, biennially shall select one of the Committee members to serve as Chairperson. The Chairperson shall be knowledgeable and experienced with regard to the administration of scientific research programs, and shall be a representative of an agency that contributes substantially, in terms of scientific research capability and budget, to the Program.
* SUPPORT PERSONNEL.-An Executive Secretary shall be apÂ­pointed by the Chairperson of the Committee, with the approval of the Committee. The Executive Secretary shall be a permanent employee of one of the agencies or departments represented on the Committee, and shall remain in the employ of such agency or department. The Chairman of the Council shall have the authority to make personnel decisions regarding any employees detailed to the Council for purposes of working on business of the Committee pursuant to section 401 of the National Science and Technology Policy, Organization, and Priorities Act of 1976 (42 U.S.C. 6651).
* CHANGE.-The Council, through the Committee, shall be responsible for planning and coÂ­ordinating the Program. In carrying out this responsibility, the Committee
	* serve as the forum for developing the Plan and for overseeing it.s implementation;
